id: pm-dfg0
title: Cursor pagination and bounded-output defaults for list/search/context at scale
description: "Bounded-output child of pm-9rxu: unbounded listings are token-catastrophic at 100k+ items. Related (not duplicate): pm-cfed lean JSON and pm-alnj search --limit shape single payloads; this defines the paging contract across read commands."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli","area:sdk",scale
created_at: "2026-07-06T21:24:55.022Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-12T16:34:14.263Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-12T16:34:13.537Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: list/search/context accept a stable cursor (--after/--cursor per ADR contract) with deterministic ordering; at-scale default limits keep any single invocation under a documented token budget with an explicit truncation marker + next-cursor hint; small workspaces see no behavior change; contracts/MCP/completions/docs regenerated
parent: pm-9rxu
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: "Delivered public SDK cursor primitives and bounded, resumable CLI output across list, search, context, and next."
expected_result: Stable query-bound cursors resume deterministic reads without duplicates while at-scale defaults bound tokens and small-workspace behavior remains compatible.
actual_result: "Cursor envelopes, --after flags, at-scale bounds, contracts, documentation, and 176 focused continuation/command tests passed locally."
